<item>
            <title>[LU-1145] Update commit-msg to allow Test-Parameters: lines to exceed 70 characters</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1145</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Test-Parameters: (&lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/ENG/Changing+Test+Parameters+with+Gerrit+Commit+Messages&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/ENG/Changing+Test+Parameters+with+Gerrit+Commit+Messages&lt;/a&gt;) line may exceed 70 characters if a large number of parameters are needed to specify the test or environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The commit message should still keep the actual line lengths at 70 characters or less, but the use of a linefeed escape &quot;\&quot; will logically concatenate those lines and any parsing of the lines, so they are exempted from the 70-character limit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13350">LU-1145</key>
